The paper introduces a new structural parameter, dependency treewidth, for the efficient solution of quantified Boolean formulas (QBF). This work involves the development of algorithms for computing the decompositions required to use the parameter. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because QBF is a well-known problem in AI, and the paper proposes a new method for solving it. It could also be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) because QBF is a logical problem, and the paper introduces a new structural parameter for solving it. Additionally, the paper involves the development of algorithms, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) because it involves the development of a new structural parameter for solving a discrete problem.
